This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on mitigating gender stereotypes in languages with rich morphology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves data augmentation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses evaluation metrics such as F1 scores and accuracies, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with languages with rich morphology, which could fall under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CY).
